rubric.description:
Students should be building an Unscented Kalman Filter basically from scratch. We'll be giving them some very light starter code but they'll be putting in the legwork with the algorithms. Their code will need to compile and come within 1% RMSE of the ground truth in order to pass. Once they get past that point, take a look at their algorithms and look for glaring inefficiencies. Their code doesn't need to extract the most of every single CPU cycle, but we expect that they do a reasonable job with practices like caching reusable values and avoiding unnecessary loops.

You can find a reviewer guide for this project [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1t4RDYFI4kcOTwLtTP_YP0vS1iPVtnkyX3HIGTEntEO4/pub?embedded=true)
